Ahead of the forthcoming Easter Celebration in commemoration of the birth, crucifixion and resurrection of Jesus Christ, the Delta State Police Command has deployed a total of five thousand eight hundred and eighty-three Police personnel for the prevention and control of crime within the state. The Police personnel are to man worship and recreation centres to ensure a crime-free celebration. The Delta State Commissioner of Police, CP Ari Muhammed Ali disclosed this in a statement signed by the Acting Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Edafe Bright. The State Police boss implored members of the public to cooperate with officers deployed, as they are under instruction to be civil, polite but firm in ensuring the security and safety of travellers and other road users throughout the state. CP Ali enjoined Christian leaders within the state to ensure that throughout the services, all Christian faithful keep to the COVID-19 protocols in their various places of worship to help the state in its fight to keep at its barest minimum cases of the disease. He also wished all Christian faithful a happy Easter celebrations in advance.